  'candidate.attempt.submit.confirm',
  'candidate',
  'en',
  'Once submitted, you cannot reopen the attempt. Verify your flagged questions first.',
  $$## Submitting your attempt

Submission is **final**. AssessIQ does not allow editing answers after
submit, and there is no second attempt unless your administrator
explicitly grants one.

Before clicking the final **Submit** button, the **Review** screen shows:

- Flagged questions you wanted to revisit.
- Unanswered questions (a blank textarea or empty MCQ counts).
- Questions whose autosave is stale (rare — usually only seconds old).

Walk through any starred or unanswered items. When you are ready, click
**Submit**. AssessIQ confirms submission with a final dialog and the
candidate timer freezes immediately.
$$,
  1,
  'active'
) ON CONFLICT (tenant_id, key, locale, version) DO NOTHING;

INSERT INTO help_content (id, tenant_id, key, audience, locale, short_text, long_md, version, status)
VALUES (
  gen_random_uuid(),
  NULL,
  'candidate.submit.confirm',
  'candidate',
  'en',
  'Final confirmation — clicking Submit ends the attempt and starts the grading queue.',
  $$## Final submit dialog

This dialog is the last step. Once you confirm, AssessIQ:

1. Freezes your answers and the timer.
2. Records all behavioral signals.
3. Queues the attempt for grading.
4. Emails your administrator that the attempt is ready for review.

**You will not see your score immediately.** AI grading runs synchronously
when an admin opens your attempt for review (Phase 1). Your administrator
will email you once the score is released; depending on their workflow,
that can be the same day or several days later.

There is no "save and continue later" option from this dialog — once you
are here, you have committed to submitting.
$$,
