) ON CONFLICT (tenant_id, key, locale, version) DO NOTHING;

INSERT INTO help_content (id, tenant_id, key, audience, locale, short_text, long_md, version, status)
VALUES (
  gen_random_uuid(),
  NULL,
  'candidate.result.bands',
  'candidate',
  'en',
  'Bands 0/25/50/75/100 represent your performance vs the rubric, not a raw percentage.',
  $$## Understanding your score

AssessIQ does not report raw percentages for subjective and scenario
questions. Instead, every answer lands on a **band**:

| Band | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **0** | Missing, off-topic, or fundamentally incorrect |
| **25** | Touched the right area but missed the key point |
| **50** | Partial credit — covered some of the rubric, missed the rest |
| **75** | Substantially correct, with one notable gap |
| **100** | Complete and well-reasoned per the rubric anchors |

**Why bands and not percentages?** Subjective work is not millimetric.
Two graders comparing "73% vs 76%" learn nothing useful; comparing band
50 vs band 75 forces a clear judgement call. AssessIQ surfaces the AI's
band, the AI's justification, and any admin override side-by-side — so
your record is transparent end-to-end.

MCQ and KQL questions also map to bands so the final score has a
consistent shape.
$$,
  1,
  'active'
) ON CONFLICT (tenant_id, key, locale, version) DO NOTHING;
